\f0\fs24 \cf0 # MYAIRCRAFT.US \'97 MASTER BUILD PROMPT\
## Unified prompt for Claude Code and Codex\
## Purpose: Build a production-grade AI-powered aircraft records, maintenance entry, and document intelligence platform\
\
You are building **myaircraft.us** as a clean, modern, production-ready web application focused on:\
\
- AI-powered aircraft maintenance record intelligence\
- Plain-English maintenance entry generation\
- Aircraft onboarding from tail number / registry lookup\
- Mechanic credential-based signing workflows\
- Smart document/photo ingestion and filing\
- FAA-aware reminders and workflow suggestions\
- One universal search bar / command bar for everything\
\
This is **not** just a chatbot.\
\
This is:\
\
**AI chat + aircraft record system + maintenance entry generator + document intelligence engine + workflow/compliance assistant**\
\
Build this with the **highest intelligence**, the cleanest structure, and solid architecture.  \
The system should feel simple on the surface, but very powerful underneath.\
\
---\
\
# 1. PRODUCT VISION\
\
Create a platform where a mechanic, owner, operator, or admin can interact with aircraft records in plain English.\
\
Examples:\
\
- \'93Prepare a 100-hour entry for N262EE starting tach 1234.56\'94\
- \'93Create an oil change entry for this aircraft\'94\
- \'93Scan this invoice and store it in the right aircraft folder\'94\
- \'93Does this maintenance note belong to airframe or engine log?\'94\
- \'93Did this work likely require an FAA form?\'94\
- \'93Show me all entries for the left engine in the last 12 months\'94\
- \'93Add aircraft N123AB and pull the registry details automatically\'94\
\
The application must be designed to reduce recordkeeping friction and make filing, generating, printing, editing, and storing entries extremely easy.\
\
---\
\
# 2. CORE PRINCIPLES\
\
## 2.1 Simplicity first\
The interface must feel dead simple.\
\
Main concept:\
- one universal search / command bar\
- one aircraft workspace\
- one document intelligence flow\
- one clean draft/preview system\
\
## 2.2 AI is assistant, not uncontrolled author\
The AI should not blindly generate permanent records with no structure.\
\
Instead:\
\
- AI interprets user intent\
- AI extracts facts\
- AI proposes wording\
- AI suggests filing destination\
- AI suggests compliance reminders\
- system validates structured fields\
- templates generate final formatted entries\
\
## 2.3 Role-based intelligence\
There are different users:\
\
- mechanic / A&P\
- IA\
- aircraft owner\
- operator\
- admin\
- viewer / general user\
\
If a user has verified mechanic credentials and permissions:\
- allow draft creation\
- allow signoff blocks\
- allow printing/export for official entries\
- allow workflow suggestions tied to mechanic role\
\
If a user is not a mechanic:\
- allow search\
- allow document upload\
- allow question asking\
- allow draft assistance\
- do not allow official signing as mechanic unless properly credentialed\
\
## 2.4 Trust and reviewability\
Everything AI-generated must remain reviewable and editable before finalization.\
\
## 2.5 Aviation-first design\
This must feel purpose-built for maintenance records and aircraft documents, not like a generic AI wrapper.\
\
---\
\
# 3. PRIMARY USER FLOWS\
\
## 3.1 Mechanic onboarding\
When a mechanic is onboarded, store a professional profile including:\
\
- full legal name\
- certificate number\
- rating(s)\
- IA status if applicable\
- signature line format\
- company / shop name\
- company logo\
- contact details\
- preferred wording style\
- permissions\
- whether they can generate printable official entries\
\
This mechanic profile should automatically populate into generated entries where appropriate.\
\
---\
\
## 3.2 Aircraft onboarding\
When a user adds an aircraft, they should be able to enter:\
\
- tail number / N-number\
- optional serial number\
- optional make/model if needed\
- optional owner/operator details\
\
The system should then:\
\
1. query an aircraft registry source/API\
2. fetch aircraft details automatically where available\
3. prefill:\
   - N-number\
   - manufacturer\
   - model\
   - serial number\
   - aircraft category/class when available\
   - engine info when available from available data sources\
   - owner/operator fields where appropriate and legally available\
4. create the aircraft record\
5. generate folder/document buckets automatically\
6. allow user review and correction before saving\
\
### Required aircraft workspace structure\
Each aircraft should have a structured document/data system like:\
\
- Overview\
- Airframe Logs\
- Engine Logs\
- Propeller Logs\
- Avionics / Appliances\
- FAA Forms\
- AD / Compliance\
- Work Orders\
- Invoices / Receipts\
- Photos / Scans\
- Generated Entries\
- Shared Records\
- Notes / Activity Timeline\
\
### Important\
Registry lookup should assist, not hard-lock the user.\
Users must be able to edit or correct aircraft details after lookup.\
\
---\
\
## 3.3 Universal AI command bar\
Create one universal command/search/chat bar that can handle all actions.\
\
Examples:\
- ask a question\
- create an entry\
- search documents\
- classify uploads\
- onboard aircraft\
- prepare a summary\
- suggest next steps\
- locate records\
- generate printable output\
\
The system should intelligently route the request behind the scenes.\
\
### Example intents\
- Q&A intent\
- create-entry intent\
- classify-document intent\
- save-document intent\
- find-record intent\
- aircraft-onboarding intent\
- compliance-suggestion intent\
- export/share intent\
\
---\
\
## 3.4 Maintenance entry creation\
This is a flagship feature.\
\
A mechanic should be able to type plain English such as:\
\
- \'93Prepare a 100-hour entry for N262EE start tach 1234.56\'94\
- \'93Create a return-to-service entry after replacing landing light\'94\
- \'93Write an oil change entry\'94\
- \'93Prepare annual inspection draft\'94\
- \'93Create discrepancy correction entry\'94\
- \'93Make a draft for left magneto replacement\'94\
\
The system must then:\
\
1. identify aircraft\
2. identify user role/credential status\
3. determine entry type\
4. extract structured facts\
5. determine missing required data\
6. ask only if absolutely needed, otherwise make a smart draft\
7. produce an editable maintenance entry draft\
8. show AI suggestions/reminders\
9. allow save / export / print / share\
10. optionally store in correct aircraft folder and activity history\
\
### Entry generation must include:\
- clean professional language\
- editable wording\
- structured metadata\
- draft status\
- role-aware signoff section\
- linked aircraft\
- linked document references if any\
- timestamps/audit trail\
\
### Important\
Do not hardcode legally risky claims.  \
Where compliance is uncertain, the UI should say things like:\
- \'93This may require review\'94\
- \'93Please verify whether Form 337 applies\'94\
- \'93Weight and balance update may be needed\'94\
- \'93Consider attaching supporting documents\'94\
\
---\
\
## 3.5 Smart document/photo ingestion\
A user should be able to:\
\
- upload PDF\
- upload image\
- take a picture from phone/camera\
- drag/drop scan\
- upload invoice/work order/log page\
\
Then the AI/document pipeline should:\
\
1. extract text\
2. detect aircraft identifiers\
3. detect date(s)\
4. detect logbook type\
5. detect whether document likely belongs to:\
   - airframe\
   - engine\
   - propeller\
   - avionics/appliance\
   - invoice\
   - work order\
   - FAA form\
   - miscellaneous\
6. detect possible related aircraft record\
7. propose filing destination\
8. summarize document for the user\
9. ask:\
   - \'93This appears to belong to N123AB \uc0\u8594  Engine Logs \u8594  save here?\'94\
10. save after confirmation\
11. create searchable metadata\
\
### If confidence is high:\
show recommendation strongly\
\
### If confidence is low:\
show top likely folders/aircraft choices\
\
---\
\
## 3.6 Editing and finalizing\
Once an entry or extracted document is generated:\
\
- user can edit text\
- user can edit structured fields\
- user can re-run suggestions\
- user can attach related files\
- user can save a new version\
- user can export/print/share\
\
Maintain versioning where possible.\
\
---\
\
## 3.7 Sharing and export\
Allow:\
- PDF export\
- print view\
- shareable secure link\
- optional PNG/image export if practical\
- save to aircraft record\
- save to generated entries\
- attach to maintenance history timeline\
\
PDF and print should be first-class.\
\
---\
\
# 4. AI + SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE\
\
Build the system as a **hybrid intelligence architecture**, not a single raw prompt chain.\
\
## 4.1 Recommended AI flow\
Use AI for:\
- natural language understanding\
- entity extraction\
- intent classification\
- document understanding\
- maintenance wording draft generation\
- summarization\
- filing suggestions\
- compliance reminders\
- search assistance\
\
Use deterministic/backend logic for:\
- permissions\
- role enforcement\
- credential gating\
- data validation\
- structured templates\
- document storage\
- export formatting\
- audit trail\
- aircraft folder logic\
- final save workflows\
\
## 4.2 Golden rule\
AI proposes.  \
System validates.  \
User reviews.  \
System stores.\
\
